==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oolite
<hw>O"o*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>w,'o`n</grk> an egg + <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ooithe</ets>.
So named from its resemblance to the roe of fish.]</ety>
<fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A variety of limestone, consisting of small
round grains, resembling the roe of a fish. It sometimes constitutes
extensive beds, as in the European Jurassic. See the <xex>Chart</xex> of
<er>Geology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oolitic</ent>⟦br⟧
